Question: How to find the sum of all values in a binary search tree?
Please using this api: TreeMap.values.
Answer:<<<api>>>: TreeMap.values
<<<code>>>: TreeMap<Integer, Integer> treeMap = new TreeMap<>();
treeMap.put(5, 5);
treeMap.put(1, 1);
treeMap.put(4, 4);
int sum = treeMap.values().stream().mapToInt(Integer::intValue).sum();
<<<explanation>>>: The values() method of the TreeMap class returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map. We then convert this to a Stream, map each Integer to its intValue, and calculate the sum.
